{%- comment -%} Ring Size Guide — Azoir {%- endcomment -%}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ 'pages.css' | asset_url }}" media="print" onload="this.media='all'">
<noscript><link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ 'pages.css' | asset_url }}"></noscript>

<section class="rsg-hero">
  <div class="ap-container">
    <span class="ap-eyebrow">Before you commission</span>
    <h1 class="rsg-hero__title">Find your perfect fit.</h1>
    <p class="rsg-hero__sub">Getting your ring size right before we begin saves time and ensures your commission arrives ready to wear. Here's how to measure with confidence.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="rsg-methods">
  <div class="ap-container">
    <h2 class="ap-section-title">Three ways to measure</h2>
    <div class="rsg-methods__grid">

      <div class="rsg-method">
        <span class="rsg-method__num">01</span>
        <h3 class="rsg-method__title">Use an existing ring</h3>
        <p class="rsg-method__body">Find a ring that fits the intended finger well. Lay it flat and measure the interior diameter in millimetres. Use the chart below to find your size.</p>
        <div class="rsg-method__tip">Best for: existing ring wearers with a well-fitting reference piece.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="rsg-method">
        <span class="rsg-method__num">02</span>
        <h3 class="rsg-method__title">Wrap with paper</h3>
        <p class="rsg-method__body">Cut a thin strip of paper and wrap it snugly around the base of the finger you intend to wear the ring on. Mark where it overlaps. Measure the length in millimetres — that's your circumference.</p>
        <div class="rsg-method__tip">Best for: measuring at home without any tools.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="rsg-method">
        <span class="rsg-method__num">03</span>
        <h3 class="rsg-method__title">Visit a local jeweller</h3>
        <p class="rsg-method__body">Any jewellery store will measure your finger with a ring gauge at no charge. Ask for your size in US and EU standards, and let us know both.</p>
        <div class="rsg-method__tip">Best for: the most accurate result, especially for wider band styles.</div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="rsg-tips-band">
  <div class="ap-container">
    <div class="rsg-tips">
      <div class="rsg-tip">
        <span class="rsg-tip__icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9711;</span>
        <p>Measure at the end of the day — fingers are slightly larger in the evening.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rsg-tip">
        <span class="rsg-tip__icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9711;</span>
        <p>Warm fingers are larger than cold ones. Measure at room temperature.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rsg-tip">
        <span class="rsg-tip__icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9711;</span>
        <p>For wide bands (over 6mm), go half a size up from your standard measurement.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rsg-tip">
        <span class="rsg-tip__icon" aria-hidden="true">&#9711;</span>
        <p>If you're between sizes, we always recommend sizing up — rings can be resized down.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

